                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><w><supplied reason="lost">ἐνθάδε</supplied></w> <w><supplied reason="lost">κῖτε</supplied></w> <persName type="attested"><name><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><lb n="2" break="no"/>νος</name></persName> <w>ζή<supplied reason="lost">σας</supplied></w> <w><supplied reason="lost">ἔτη</supplied></w> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="3"/><w>ἀμέμπ<supplied reason="lost">τως</supplied></w> <w><supplied reason="lost">τελευτᾷ</supplied></w>
                    <lb n="4"/><w>τῇ</w> <w>πρὸ</w> <hi rend="supraline"><num value="14">ιδ</num></hi> <w><supplied reason="lost">καλανδῶν</supplied></w>
                    <lb n="5"/><w><expan><abbr>Μαρτ</abbr><ex>ίων</ex></expan></w> <w>ἡμέρ<supplied reason="lost">ᾳ</supplied></w> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus" resp="#martaf">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text based on photograph</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 1"><note>Ferrua: [κεῖται]; Korhonen: [κῖτε]</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 5"><note>In the lacuna, a day of the week should be mentioned</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#martaf">
                <p>Here lies -nos, having lived for ... years blamelessly. He died 14 days before the kalends of March on the day of…</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#martaf">
                <p>Qui giace -nos, avendo vissuto ... anni senza colpa. Morì 14 giorni prima delle Calende di marzo, nel giorno di …</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#martaf">
                <p>This Christian epitaph has the traditional structure with the <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἐνθάδε κεῖται</foreign> formula, the name of the deceased (here in the lacuna) followed by his age and by another independent sentence with the day of death (with the present of <foreign xml:lang="grc">τελευτάω</foreign>), as recurring in other inscriptions from Catania, such as IG 14.556 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001375">ISic001375</ref>. In the lacuna there should also have been the specification of the day of the week (<foreign xml:lang="grc">ἡμέρ[ᾳ---]</foreign>).</p>
            </div>
